{"title_page": "List of games using procedural generation", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Inc-vg| with [[Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources|reliably sourced]] entries for [[Wikipedia:Notability|notable]] games}}\n\nThis is a list of video games that make at least partial use of [[procedural generation]] to create their maps and levels, or other similar features. <!--Information regarding date of release, developer, platform, genre and notability is provided when available.--> By default, the table is sorted chronologically, but the sorting factor may be selected by clicking on the small boxes next to the column headings.\n\n==List==\n===Roguelike games===\n{{see|List of roguelikes}}\nGames in the [[roguelike]] genre all have at least procedurally generated levels.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/299316/7_roguelikes_that_every_developer_should_study.php|title=7 roguelikes that every developer should study|last=Fogel|first=Stefanie|website=www.gamasutra.com|language=en|access-date=2019-06-16}}</ref>\n\n===Other===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|-\n! width=\"20%\"| Title\n! Year\n! width=\"20%\"| Developer(s)\n! width=\"60%\"| Procedural content\n|-\n| ''[[Banished (video game)|Banished]]''\n| 2014\n| Shining Rock Software\n| Terrain map.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2014-02-25-banished-review|title=Banished review|first=Paul|last=Dean|date=28 February 2014|publisher=|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Borderlands (series)|''Borderlands'' series]]\n| 2009\u20132019\n| [[Gearbox Software]], [[2K Australia]]\n| Weapons.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2012-07-16-how-many-weapons-are-in-borderlands-2|title=How many weapons are in Borderlands 2?|author=|date=|website=eurogamer.net}}</ref>\n\n|-\n| [[Civilization (series)|''Civilization'' series]]\n| 1991\u20132018\n| [[MicroProse]], [[Activision]], [[Firaxis Games]]\n| Customizable flat world map.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/5489814/civilization-v-preview-small-changes-big-differences|title=Civilization V Preview: Small Changes, Big Differences|first=Stephen|last=Totilo|date=|website=kotaku.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Crypt of the NecroDancer]]''\n| 2015\n| Brace Yourself Games\n| 2D grid-based top-down dungeons with halls and rooms<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/04/24/review-crypt-of-the-necrodancer/145786/|title=Review: Crypt of the NecroDancer|date=24 April 2015|website=Hardcore Gamer|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/crypt-of-the-necrodancer-review/|title=Crypt of the Necrodancer review|first=Chris|last=Thursten|date=12 May 2015|publisher=|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2015-07-10-crypt-of-the-necrodancer-to-get-jiggy-on-ps4-and-vita|title=Crypt of the NecroDancer to get jiggy on PS4 and Vita|first=Jeffrey|last=Matulef|date=10 July 2015|publisher=|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref> with randomly placed enemies and items.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamezebo.com/2016/07/06/crypt-necrodancer-review-disco-inferno/|title=Crypt of the NecroDancer Review: Disco Inferno|first=Rob Rich|last=https://www.gamezebo.com/author/rob-rich|date=6 July 2016|publisher=|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Deep Rock Galactic]]''\n| 2018\n| [[Ghost Ship Games]]\n| Cave systems separated into rooms and tunnels by walls of dirt.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2018/03/19/how-deep-rock-galactic-mines-fun-from-absolute-darkess/|title=How Deep Rock Galactic mines fun from absolute darkness|date=19 March 2018|website=Rock Paper Shotgun|accessdate=26 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Descenders (video game)|Descenders]]''\n| 2018\n| RageSquid\n| 3D downhill courses on relatively dirt trails.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/downhill-biking-game-descenders-could-be-the-heir-to-skates-throne/ |title=Downhill biking game Descenders could be the heir to Skate's throne |last=Bowman |first=Mitch |date=2018-02-09 |website=PC Gamer |language=en-US |access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Don't Starve]]''\n| 2013\n| [[Klei Entertainment]]\n| Flat 2D world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2013/04/26/dont-starve-review/|title=Wot I Think: Don\u2019t Starve|author=|date=|website=rockpapershotgun.com}}</ref> Later expanded with cavern systems<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/dont-starve-update-adds-caves-and-bunnies/|title=Don't Starve update adds caves and bunnies|author=|date=|website=pcgamer.com}}</ref> and oceans.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/dont-starve-shipwrecked-is-a-breath-of-fresh-nope-thats-a-hurricane/|title=Don\u2019t Starve: Shipwrecked is a breath of fresh\u2026 Nope, that\u2019s a hurricane|author=|date=|website=pcgamer.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Dwarf Fortress]]''\n| 2006\n| [[Tarn Adams]]\n| Almost entirety of game content<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/dwarf-fortress-creator-on-how-hes-42-towards-simulating-existence/|title=Dwarf Fortress' creator on how he's 42% towards simulating existence|author=|date=|website=pcgamer.com}}</ref> based in a layered 3D world with elements like its history,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2014/7/23/5926447/dwarf-fortress-will-crush-your-cpu-because-creating-history-is-hard|title=Dwarf Fortress will crush your CPU because creating history is hard|author=|date=|website=polygon.com}}</ref> creatures and narrative,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/24/magazine/the-brilliance-of-dwarf-fortress.html|title=The Brilliance of Dwarf Fortress|first=Jonah|last=Weiner|date=|website=nytimes.com}}</ref> religion,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2016/08/05/how-to-procedurally-generate-religion-politics/|title=Generation Next, Part 2: How To Generate A Religion|author=|date=|website=rockpapershotgun.com}}</ref> etc.\n|-\n| ''[[Enter the Gungeon]]''\n| 2016\n| Dodge Roll\n| 2D flat dungeon levels made of room \"chunks\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/enter-the-gungeon-pc-review|title=Enter the Gungeon PC Review: A Fistful of Bullets|author=|date=|website=USgamer.net}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Baldi's Basics Plus]]''\n| 2020\n| Basically Games\n| Randomly generates a school as well as random characters (off of a list) random events and more.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.basicallygames.com|title=Basically Games website|author=|date=|website=basicallygames.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Left 4 Dead 2]]''\n| 2009\n| [[Valve Corporation|Valve]]\n| Gameplay changes to match player's performance, such as enemies, paths, or weather.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2009/06/01/left-4-dead-2-exclusive-rps-preview/|title=Left 4 Dead 2: Exclusive RPS Hands-On Preview|first=John|last=Walker|date=1 June 2009|publisher=|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Minecraft]]''\n| 2011\n| [[Mojang]]\n| 3D world primarily made of cube blocks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2015/03/04/how-minecraft-worlds-are-made/|title=Here's how 'Minecraft' creates its gigantic worlds|author=|date=|website=engadget.com}}</ref> Effectively infinite.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/minecraft/just-how-big-minecraft-world-big-it-turns-out|title=Just how big is a Minecraft world? Big, as it turns out.|author=|date=|website=PCGamesN}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Minecraft Dungeons]]''\n| ''2020''\n| [[Mojang]]\n| Randomly-generated 3D dungeons filled with monsters, traps and puzzles, and treasures.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/06/11/minecraft-dungeons-is-a-blocky-smash-and-slash-adventure/|title='Minecraft Dungeons' is a blocky, smash-and-slash adventure|website=Engadget|language=en|access-date=2019-06-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/e3/2019/6/10/18660635/minecraft-dungeons-release-date-xbox-one-pc-ps4-e3-2019|title=Minecraft Dungeons is simple, Diablo-inspired fun for the family|last=Campbell|first=Colin|date=2019-06-10|website=Polygon|access-date=2019-06-11}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Mini Metro (video game)|Mini Metro]]''\n| 2015\n| Dinosaur Polo Club\n| Abstract 2D levels and audio system.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/273284/Postmortem_Dinosaur_Polo_Clubs_Mini_Metro.php|title=Postmortem: Dinosaur Polo Club's Mini Metro|first=Peter|last=Curry|website=www.gamasutra.com|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[No Man's Sky]]''\n| 2016\n| [[Hello Games]]\n| 3D galaxies with planets and their flora and fauna.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/no-mans-sky-revisited/|title=After two years, is No Man's Sky everything Hello Games originally promised?|author=|date=|website=gamesradar.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/a-look-at-how-no-mans-skys-procedural-generation-works-1787928446|title=A Look At How No Man's Sky's Procedural Generation Works|first=Heather|last=Alexandra|date=|website=kotaku.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Pixel Piracy]]''\n| 2015\n| Quadro Delta\n| 2D world,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamezone.com/news/pirate-simulator-pixel-piracy-headed-to-xbox-one-and-ps4-3432534/|title=Pirate simulator Pixel Piracy headed to Xbox One and PS4|first=Mike|last=Boccher|date=21 January 2016|publisher=|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref> including islands, towns and shops, as well as ship's crew.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.player.one/pixel-piracy-review-what-shall-we-do-drunken-sailor-376736|title=Pixel Piracy Review: What Shall We Do With The Drunken Sailor?|date=11 August 2014|website=Player.One|accessdate=23 January 2019}}</ref><!--Still need to cite stuff like events, dungeons, etc.-->\n|-\n| ''[[RimWorld]]''\n| 2013 (EA)\n| Ludeon Studios\n| Customization 3D spherical world map and flat 2D gameplay map,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2016/12/20/rimworld-wanderlust-update/|title=RimWorld\u2019s huge Wanderlust update is world-changing|author=|date=|webs