ch 2018|website=Rock Paper Shotgun|accessdate=26 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Descenders (video game)|Descenders]]''\n| 2018\n| RageSquid\n| 3D downhill courses on relatively dirt trails.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pcgamer.com/downhill-biking-game-descenders-could-be-the-heir-to-skates-throne/ |title=Downhill biking game Descenders could be the heir to Skate's throne |last=Bowman |first=Mitch |date=2018-02-09 |website=PC Gamer |language=en-US |access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Don't Starve]]''\n| 2013\n| [[Klei Entertainment]]\n| Flat 2D world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2013/04/26/dont-starve-review/|title=Wot I Think: Don\u2019t Starve|author=|date=|website=rockpapershotgun.com}}</ref> Later expanded with cavern systems<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/dont-starve-update-adds-caves-and-bunnies/|title=Don't Starve update adds caves and bunnies|author=|date=|website=pcgamer.com}}</ref> and oceans.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/dont-starve-shipwrecked-is-a-breath-of-fresh-nope-thats-a-hurricane/|title=Don\u2019t Starve: Shipwrecked is a breath of fresh\u2026 Nope, that\u2019s a hurricane|author=|date=|website=pcgamer.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Dwarf Fortress]]''\n| 2006\n| [[Tarn Adams]]\n| Almost entirety of game content<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/dwarf-fortress-creator-on-how-hes-42-towards-simulating-existence/|title=Dwarf Fortress' creator on how he's 42% towards simulating existence|author=|date=|website=pcgamer.com}}</ref> based in a layered 3D world with elements like its history,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2014/7/23/5926447/dwarf-fortress-will-crush-your-cpu-because-creating-history-is-hard|title=Dwarf Fortress will crush your CPU because creating history is hard|author=|date=|website=polygon.com}}</ref> creatures and narrative,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/24/magazine/the-brilliance-of-dwarf-fortress.html|title=The Brilliance of Dwarf Fortress|fi