le=Dit is getrained zeilen\n   |language=Dutch\n   |publisher=De Boer Maritiem\n   |publication-date=1978\n   |pages=16\u201317\n   |isbn=90 228 1166 2\n }}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Outer, Rudy den}}\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:Dutch male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Flying Dutchman class sailors]]\n[[Category:Tempest class sailors]]\n[[Category:North American Champion Soling]]\n[[Category:Dragon class sailors]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Rotterdam]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox sailor\n  | name           = Rudy den Outer\n  | image          = Fred Imhoff in the Dragon NED 247.jpg\n  | image_size     = 200px\n  | caption        = The team of Fred Imhoff, Richard van Rij & Rudy den Outer sailing the Dragon ''Danish Joker''.\n  | birth_name     =\n  | fullname       = Rudy den Outer\n  | nickname       =\n  | nationality    = Dutch\n  | birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1954|07|22}}\n  | birth_place    = [[Rotterdam]]\n  | death_date     =\n  | death_place    =\n  | height         = {{convert|1.86|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n  | weight         =\n  | retired        =\n  | classes        = [[Flying Dutchman (dinghy)|Flying Dutchman]]<br />[[Tempest (keelboat)|Tempest]]<br />[[Soling]]<br />[[Dragon (keelboat)|Dragon]]\n  | club           = [[:nl:Kralingsche Zeil Club|Kralingsche Zeil Club]]\n  | collegeteam    =\n  | coach          =\n  | medaltemplates-title =\n  | medaltemplates = \n    {{Medal|Country|{{NED}}}}\n      {{MedalCompetition|[[Vintage Yachting Games]]}}\n        {{Medal|Gold|[[2008 Vintage Yachting Games|2008 Medemblik]]|[[2008 Vintage Yachting Games \u2013 Soling|Soling]]<ref name=\"E\" />}}\n        {{Medal|Silver|[[2012 Vintage Yachting Games|2012 Bellano]]|[[2012 Vintage Yachting Games \u2013 Soling|Soling]]<ref name=\"F\" />}}\n        {{Medal|Gold|[[2018 Vintage Yachting Games|2018 Hellerup]]|[[2018 Vintage Yachting Games \u2013 Soling|Soling]]<ref name=\"G\" />}}\n      {{MedalCompetition|European Championships}}\n        {{Medal|Gold|2003 Kinsale|[[Dragon (keelboat)|Dragon]]<ref name=\"J\" /><ref name=\"K\" /><ref name=\"L\" /><ref name=\"M\" />}}\n        {{Medal|Bronze|2012 Aarhus|Soling<ref name=\"Q\" />}}\n        {{Medal|Bronze|2014 Quiberon|Soling<ref name=\"S\" />}}\n      {{MedalCompetition|North American Championships}}\n        {{Medal|Gold|2019 Kingston, Ontario|Soling<ref name=\"T\" />}}\n      {{MedalCompetition|[[Dragon Gold Cup]]}}\n        {{Medal|Silver|2002 Mariehamn|Dragon}}\n  | show-medals    = yes\n  | updated        = 8-OCT-2015\n}}\n\n[[File:VYG 1 Soling 2008.JPG|thumb|left|Rudy den Outer, Leo Determan and Ronald den Arend winning the [[2008 Vintage Yachting Games]] in [[Medemblik]].]]\n\n'''Rudy den Outer''' (born 22 July 1954 in [[Rotterdam]]<ref name=A />) is a [[sailor]] from the Netherlands, who represented his country at the [[2008 Vintage Yachting Games \u2013 Soling|2008 Vintage Yachting Games]] in [[Medemblik]], as helmsman in the Dutch [[Soling]] ''Sophie\u2019s Choice''. Den Outer with crew members [[Leo Determan]] and [[Ronald den Arend]] took the Gold. In the [[2012 Vintage Yachting Games \u2013 Soling|2012 Vintage Yachting Games]], this time with crew members [[Gavin Lidlow]] and [[Ramzi Souli]] the team took the Silver medal in [[Bellano]], Italy. In 2003 with helmsman [[Fred Imhoff]] and [[Richard van Rij]] he became European Champion in the [[Dragon (keelboat)#Wall of Fame|Dragon]] at [[Kinsale]], Ireland.<ref name=\"D\" /> Den Outer is also very active in the organization of major International Sailing events for Olympic and former Olympic classes.\n\n== Sailing career ==\n[[File:FD H125.jpg|left|thumb|Leo Determan and Rudy den Outer (left) in the Flying Dutchman ''Aquarius'' on the Kralingsche Plas, Netherlands in 1970]]\nRudy den Outer, after sailing some Dutch National classes, started his International sailing in 1970 crewing for Leo Determan in the [[Flying Dutchman (dinghy)|Flying Dutchman]]. In 1975, Den Outer crewed for [[Ben Staartjes]] in the [[Tempest (keelboat)|Tempest]].<ref name=\"AA\" /> He was member of the \u201cYellow Joker\u201d sailing team of [[Fred Imhoff]].<ref name=\"AB\" /> den Outer helmed in the [[Soling World Championships|1987 Soling World Championship]].<ref name=\"Z\" />  During 1999 and 2001, Den Outer crewed for [[Heike Blok]] in the [[Dragon (keelboat)|Dragon]]. He was part of helmsman Fred Imhoff's Dragon crew along with [[Richard van Rij]] that won the 2003 Dragon European Championship.<ref name=\"L\" />  During the [[2018 Vintage Yachting Games|2018 Vintage]] the Soling team of Rudy den Outer, [[Theo de Lange]] and [[Gabor Helmhout]] took the gold during challenging circumstances off the coast of [[Hellerup]], [[Denmark]]. In 2019 den Outer as helmsman with Theo de Lange and [[Thies Bosch]] took the gold during the [[Soling North American Championship results (2010\u201319)#2019 Final results|2019 North American Championship 2019]] on [[Lake Ontario]], [[Kingston, Ontario]]. Den Outer is sailing Soling on regular basis in National and International competitions as member of the [[:nl:Kralingsche Zeil Club|Kralingsche Zeil Club]] in Rotterdam.\n\n== Regatta organization and management==\nRudy den Outer organized the [[Soling#Worlds Fleetrace Championship|1990 Soling World Championship]] (fleetrace) in [[Medemblik]] with the [[Hollandia Roeiclub|Royal Yachtclub Hollandia]], the [[Soling#European Matchrace Championship|1993 Soling European Championship]], and the [[Soling#Worlds Matchrace Championship (Infanta Cristina)|1988 Soling World Championship]] (both matchrace) at [[Rotterdam]], [[Kralingen]] this in cooperation with the [[:nl:Kralingse Plas|Rotterdamsche Zeilvereeniging]]. Den Outer took in 2006 the initiative<ref name=C /> for the [[Vintage Yachting Games]].<ref name=\"X\" /> This event for the former Olympic classes is held every four years. Currently Den Outer is chairman<ref name=B /> of the daily board of the Vintage Yachting Games Organization. He is past committee member of the [[International Soling Association]] 3 terms from 1988<ref name=\"U\" /> till 1997<ref name=\"V\" /> and Past Vice-President from the same organization (1993).<ref name=\"W\" />\n\n== Personal life ==\nDen Outer studied Science and Mathematics in [[Delft]]. He is married with Sophie van den Berge and works as program and project manager within the IT industry.<ref name=A />\n{{Footer North American Champions Soling}}\n{{Footer Winners Vintage Yachting Games}}\n{{Netherlands-yachtracing-bio-stub}}\n{{clear}}\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs =\n <ref name=A>{{cite web\n   |url        = http://www.linkedin.com/in/rudydenouter\n   |title      = Rudy den Outer CV\n   |publisher  = www.linkedin.org\n   |accessdate = 30 January 2014\n  }}</ref>\n <ref name=B>{{cite web\n   |url        = http://vintageyachtinggames.org/ITA2012/?page_id=2\n   |title      = Vintage Yachting Games Organization\n   |publisher  = \n   |accessdate = 30 January 2014\n  }}</ref>\n <ref name=C>{{cite web\n   |url        = http://www.sailifdco.com/interview-with-rudy-den-outer\n   |title      = Interview with Rudy den Outer\n   |publisher  = sailIFDCO.org\n   |accessdate = 30 January 2014\n  }}</ref>\n <ref name=D>{{cite web\n   |url        = http://www.yachtsandyachting.com/news/10829\n   |title      = Dragon Europeans at Kinsale Yacht Club Overall\n   |date       = 24 August 2003\n   |publisher  = Yachts and Yachting\n   |accessdate = 8 April 2015\n  }}</ref>\n <ref name=E>{{cite web\n   |url=http://www.soling.com/results/ShowResults.asp?ID=459\n   |title=Vintage Yachting Games 2008\n   |year=2008\n   |website=www.soling.com\n   |publisher=International Soling Association|location=Buenos Aires (ARG)\n   |access-date=8 April 2015\n }}</ref>\n <ref name=F>{{cite web\n   |url=http://www.soling.com/results/ShowResults.asp?ID=623\n   |title=Vintage Yachting Games 2012\n   |year=2012|website=www.soling.com\n   |publisher=Internat